               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-1402" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1402" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1402" type="surname" value="BATES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1402" type="given" value="AMELIA"></interp>AMELIA BATES.</persName>
                  </hi> I am nearly eleven years old—I live with my father, James Bates. I recollect going out to play at the Belvidere ruins—I saw John Booth and another little boy there, and the prisoner and a boy a little bigger than him—the prisoner and the other boy took little Booth into a privy, sat him on the seat, and took off his boots—the boy cried—the prisoner said, "If you do not hold your tongue I will take and hit you"—he took out a knife to cut off the child's fingers—I saw the prisoner go away, I caught him—I knew him by sight—the other punched me on the head and got away—I saw the little boy afterwards—he had no boots on.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
